Gorbachev said Tuesday in Moscow that he believed one Germany was likely in the future, but he added that Germans "should not decide this important question on the streets."
He referred to the growing number of demonstrations in East Germany in support of reunification.
East German Communists on Tuesday endorsed for reunification for the first time.
Party ideologist Peter Brie said the Communists support "the togetherness of the German nation," and urged a thoughtful and measured approach to reunification.
